1
00:00:26,740 --> 00:00:29,730
♪Memory is like reflection in the mirror♪

2
00:00:29,730 --> 00:00:32,790
♪Ephemeral yet lasting in the heart♪

3
00:00:32,790 --> 00:00:36,110
♪I let go of worries and face the road ahead♪

4
00:00:36,110 --> 00:00:39,410
♪The vast land stretches far and wide♪

5
00:00:39,410 --> 00:00:42,400
♪My heart remains strong, spirit unbroken♪

6
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:45,540
♪May this life remain unscathed,
till we meet again♪

7
00:00:45,540 --> 00:00:48,880
♪With calm laughter, I vanquish evil♪

8
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:52,030
♪Together, we walk through life hand in hand♪

9
00:00:52,190 --> 00:00:55,480
♪Dust rises♪

10
00:00:55,480 --> 00:00:58,280
♪The melody continues amidst the turmoil♪

11
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:02,910
♪We stand firm in the wind side by side♪

12
00:01:03,120 --> 00:01:06,740
♪I dream as if all is but a fleeting moment♪

13
00:01:06,740 --> 00:01:09,180
♪Yet life rarely follows our desires♪

14
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:15,520
♪With the totem of strength,
I endure many trials♪

15
00:01:15,890 --> 00:01:19,460
♪Cross love and hate, life and death♪

16
00:01:19,460 --> 00:01:22,240
♪We fight with heads held high♪

17
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:26,040
♪Facing the chasm of life♪

18
00:01:26,290 --> 00:01:30,610
♪We stand tall fearlessly♪

19
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:35,980
=Fateful Love=

20
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:38,980
=Episode 28=

21
00:01:57,270 --> 00:01:58,110
Ziqing.

22
00:01:58,910 --> 00:01:59,750
Ziqing.

23
00:02:11,290 --> 00:02:15,250
♪When the drifting clouds fall in love
with the fierce wind♪

24
00:02:16,710 --> 00:02:17,650
Haonan.

25
00:02:18,230 --> 00:02:19,850
Qianqian, are you okay?

26
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:22,600
Let's go.

27
00:02:26,810 --> 00:02:30,480
♪Blame the heavens
for deliberately playing tricks♪

28
00:02:30,710 --> 00:02:33,920
♪Making our encounter too brief♪

29
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:35,800
What happened?

30
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:37,420
Four Princess is buried underneath.

31
00:02:38,070 --> 00:02:38,910
Help!

32
00:02:40,340 --> 00:02:43,140
♪Promise♪

33
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:47,730
♪Who promised to ride across the world♪

34
00:02:48,580 --> 00:02:51,040
♪Crossing the vast desert sands♪

35
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:54,340
♪Deceiving me
with a lifetime of longing♪

36
00:02:54,630 --> 00:02:55,700
What's wrong with you?

37
00:02:56,350 --> 00:02:58,130
You don't change color,
nor do you dig the sand.

38
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:01,040
What's the matter?

39
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:03,110
When Ziqing hadn't fallen,

40
00:03:03,110 --> 00:03:04,650
you kept digging into the sand.

41
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,550
As soon as Ziqing fell,

42
00:03:06,550 --> 00:03:07,620
you stopped digging.

43
00:03:07,990 --> 00:03:09,340
What do you mean by this?

44
00:03:10,350 --> 00:03:11,190
Tell me.

45
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,160
You're completely useless.

46
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:14,000
I'll dig by myself.

47
00:03:16,150 --> 00:03:17,290
Jun Beiyue.

48
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:18,900
You're still alive.

49
00:03:20,230 --> 00:03:21,360
Let go.

50
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,290
- Why are you here?
- Let go.

51
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:24,440
No, what's going on?
What are you trying to do?

52
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:25,670
If he cared about Ziqing,

53
00:03:25,670 --> 00:03:26,990
Ziqing wouldn't have had the accident.

54
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:32,390
Why are you holding a sword?

55
00:03:32,390 --> 00:03:33,800
Calm down.

56
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:34,800
Ziqing has already fallen.

57
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,190
He knew Ziqing's background well,

58
00:03:36,190 --> 00:03:37,930
so why didn't he protect her properly?

59
00:03:38,790 --> 00:03:40,770
Now he's just pretending here.

60
00:03:43,410 --> 00:03:44,250
Let go of me.

61
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:46,160
Don't go.

62
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:48,110
The most urgent thing now
is to find Ziqing, isn't it?

63
00:03:48,110 --> 00:03:48,960
What's done is done.

64
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,240
If you kill him or he kills you,

65
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,100
will Ziqing come out?

66
00:03:51,790 --> 00:03:53,290
Are you out of your mind?

67
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:57,270
Ziqing couldn't have just fallen

68
00:03:57,270 --> 00:03:58,460
for no reason.

69
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:00,600
There must be something fishy about it.

70
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:01,440
Do you understand?

71
00:04:02,710 --> 00:04:04,000
Oh right.

72
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:04,840
Archive Pavilion.

73
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:06,290
The Archive Pavilion in Nanzhao.

74
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,110
It must have records

75
00:04:08,110 --> 00:04:09,370
about Mingsha Mountain.

76
00:04:09,790 --> 00:04:10,630
Come with me.

77
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:13,340
I need to stay here to find Ziqing.

78
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,550
Then you dig here.

79
00:04:15,550 --> 00:04:16,610
I'm leaving. I'll go by myself.

80
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,540
If anything happens to Ziqing,

81
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,980
I will never forgive you.

82
00:04:24,930 --> 00:04:29,480
♪Only the fragrance remains
on my fingertips♪

83
00:04:43,740 --> 00:04:47,540
♪Don't ask who left the longing♪

84
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:51,210
♪It turned into a scar♪

85
00:04:51,430 --> 00:04:56,910
♪Leading me far away,
the wind accompanies you to the end♪

86
00:04:59,070 --> 00:05:03,230
♪Who left a touch of makeup♪

87
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:07,220
♪Like quicksand falling
through my fingers♪

88
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:11,740
♪As if in a moment, only the fragrance
remains on my fingertips♪

89
00:05:11,910 --> 00:05:12,750
Your Highness.

90
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:15,300
What's wrong, Your Highness?

91
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,150
- Your Highness.
- Your Highness.

92
00:05:17,310 --> 00:05:18,510
- Your Highness.
- Your Highness.

93
00:05:18,510 --> 00:05:19,350
Your Highness!

94
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:21,490
Wake up.

95
00:05:22,790 --> 00:05:24,020
Wake up, Your Highness.

96
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:25,960
Your Highness.

97
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:27,920
Quick, go get Physician Gu.

98
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:28,760
Yes.

99
00:05:33,350 --> 00:05:34,190
Go.

100
00:05:43,980 --> 00:05:46,380
(Yue)

101
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:05,300
What's going on?

102
00:08:06,310 --> 00:08:07,170
Why am I still here?

103
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:30,420
Let go of me!

104
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:34,130
Let go!

105
00:08:46,670 --> 00:08:47,650
Let go of me!

106
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,250
Han Ziqing,

107
00:09:02,170 --> 00:09:03,860
stop struggling.

108
00:09:04,310 --> 00:09:06,160
The Isolated Island's bloodline

109
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:07,740
is evil.

110
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:12,100
You were never meant to exist
on Longyuan Continent

111
00:09:12,870 --> 00:09:14,620
Exile yourself,

112
00:09:14,990 --> 00:09:17,240
and you can gain freedom.

113
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,380
Gain freedom?

114
00:09:21,870 --> 00:09:23,190
Can you take me away from here?

115
00:09:23,190 --> 00:09:24,940
Of course, I can.

116
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:27,860
You can go anywhere you want.

117
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:30,130
Trust me.

118
00:09:30,990 --> 00:09:32,540
I'm helping you.

119
00:09:43,990 --> 00:09:46,400
Who are you?

120
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:47,920
Why are you helping me?

121
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:50,010
It is not important.

122
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:52,740
What matters is who you are.

123
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:55,380
You are an Islander.

124
00:09:56,870 --> 00:09:58,590
This Poisonous Grass World

125
00:09:58,590 --> 00:10:00,250
exists because of you.

126
00:10:01,110 --> 00:10:02,650
You should accept it

127
00:10:03,190 --> 00:10:05,570
and become stronger here.

128
00:10:07,110 --> 00:10:10,210
Being a Human Puppet
is your ultimate destiny.

129
00:10:10,670 --> 00:10:11,740
I am not a Human Puppet.

130
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,650
I am not an Islander.

131
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:15,770
I am not Han Ziqing.

132
00:10:16,670 --> 00:10:18,440
I am myself.

133
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:19,880
I am myself.

134
00:10:19,880 --> 00:10:21,300
Myself!

135
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:41,860
(This girl is so hard to tame.)

136
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:45,130
(The entrance to the Barrier
is now closed.)

137
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:48,980
(It seems I have to make other plans.)

138
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,000
Ten, Your Highness is suffering
from a rush of anger.

139
00:10:59,000 --> 00:10:59,910
He is having a fever.

140
00:10:59,910 --> 00:11:00,880
Take good care of him.

141
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:02,520
- I'll go prepare some medicine.
- Yes.

142
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:03,380
Shadow, come with me.

143
00:12:00,550 --> 00:12:01,390
Your Highness.

144
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,100
Ziqing.

145
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:10,000
Ziqing,

146
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,890
you're back.

147
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:34,420
Your Highness.

148
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:12,560
Who is it?

149
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:14,330
Come out right now.

150
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:16,330
I'll count to three.

151
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:18,640
If you don't come out,

152
00:14:18,640 --> 00:14:20,100
don't blame me for being rude.

153
00:14:23,040 --> 00:14:24,300
My books!

154
00:14:26,110 --> 00:14:27,300
My books!

155
00:14:28,190 --> 00:14:30,540
This is going to kill me.

156
00:14:30,990 --> 00:14:32,940
Who is it?
If you have the guts, come out.

157
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:38,200
Master Jin, don't be anxious.
I'll come out.

158
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:39,500
Baili Weisheng.

159
00:14:40,070 --> 00:14:40,980
Why are you here?

160
00:14:41,510 --> 00:14:43,880
You trespassed into Archive Pavilion,
the forbidden area.

161
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:45,060
Do you wish to die?

162
00:14:46,070 --> 00:14:48,350
Don't be hasty.

163
00:14:48,350 --> 00:14:49,520
I just missed you.

164
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:50,840
I wanted to come see you.

165
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:52,420
Do we have any relationship?

166
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,250
How you would come to see me?

167
00:14:54,870 --> 00:14:56,710
This is the royal forbidden area.

168
00:14:56,710 --> 00:14:59,000
You must be up to no good
to trespass here.

169
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,570
Keep your voice down.

170
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:02,650
If my hand shakes,

171
00:15:03,070 --> 00:15:04,440
these hundred-year-old books

172
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:06,280
may be burned down by fire.

173
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,320
Baili Weisheng,

174
00:15:07,320 --> 00:15:08,890
what exactly do you want?

175
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:11,230
Master Jin,

176
00:15:11,230 --> 00:15:14,150
I just want to find a book
in Archive Pavilion.

177
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:15,740
Why don't you help me look for it?

178
00:15:16,870 --> 00:15:18,210
You brat

179
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:20,940
snoop around Archive Pavilion.

180
00:15:21,510 --> 00:15:23,590
I think you're tired of living.

181
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:25,210
I'll report this to His Majesty
immediately.

182
00:15:27,990 --> 00:15:29,210
Wait, wait.

183
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:30,980
Put the fire away.

184
00:15:31,670 --> 00:15:32,550
Put it away.

185
00:15:32,550 --> 00:15:33,520
Don't come any closer.

186
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:35,860
Or I'll really set it on fire.

187
00:15:36,920 --> 00:15:38,890
Let's talk this over.

188
00:15:39,430 --> 00:15:40,270
You brat,

189
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:43,110
setting fire to Archive Pavilion

190
00:15:43,110 --> 00:15:45,550
is a crime punishable
by flaying and dismemberment.

191
00:15:45,550 --> 00:15:47,180
You better think it over.

192
00:15:47,670 --> 00:15:48,620
Master Jin,

193
00:15:49,430 --> 00:15:51,110
for the sake of our old acquaintance,

194
00:15:51,110 --> 00:15:52,520
just tell me

195
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:54,350
where the book

196
00:15:54,350 --> 00:15:55,360
about Mingsha Mountain is.

197
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:56,540
I won't burn your books anymore.

198
00:15:57,070 --> 00:15:58,450
Mingsha Mountain?

199
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:00,080
What are you going there for?

200
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:02,110
Is there something strange
about Mingsha Mountain?

201
00:16:02,110 --> 00:16:03,180
How would I know?

202
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,860
Is there something in Mingsha Mountain?

203
00:16:06,630 --> 00:16:08,890
For example,

204
00:16:09,990 --> 00:16:13,980
is it a secret chamber full of poisons?

205
00:16:16,420 --> 00:16:18,200
I only handle herb gathering
and medicine refining.

206
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,850
How would I know anything
about secret chambers?

207
00:16:19,850 --> 00:16:21,470
I'm not from Meng Tribe.

208
00:16:21,470 --> 00:16:24,060
How could I possibly create a Barrier
for a secret chamber out of thin air?

209
00:16:25,670 --> 00:16:26,510
Barrier?

210
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:28,250
Are you saying

211
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:31,320
there's a Barrier
under Mingsha Mountain?

212
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:32,640
You said

213
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:34,670
there's a secret chamber
under Mingsha Mountain.

214
00:16:34,670 --> 00:16:36,130
I just remembered it.

215
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:41,620
There must be a book

216
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:44,620
about the Barrier at Mingsha Mountain.

217
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:46,000
in Archive Pavilion.

218
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:46,980
No, no.

219
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:49,500
There's nothing. You should leave.

220
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:51,760
Otherwise, I'll call the guards.

221
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:54,320
I knew you wouldn't help me.

222
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:55,210
Luckily, I'm smart.

223
00:16:55,670 --> 00:16:57,100
I've already found it myself.

224
00:17:04,240 --> 00:17:05,660
You brat.

225
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:09,450
Could he take it?

226
00:17:18,310 --> 00:17:19,680
You brat,

227
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:21,230
how dare you deceive me.

228
00:17:21,230 --> 00:17:22,070
Thanks.

229
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:24,200
Stop right there.

230
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:32,810
You brat, stop right there.

231
00:17:41,390 --> 00:17:44,160
You brat, you've been hit
by my Seven Insect Powder.

232
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,470
Do you still want to get away unscathed?

233
00:17:45,470 --> 00:17:46,570
Go to hell!

234
00:18:06,070 --> 00:18:07,140
Luckily, you protected me.

235
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:08,360
Without you,

236
00:18:09,550 --> 00:18:10,860
this arm would be useless.

237
00:18:12,190 --> 00:18:14,050
What a Golden Merfolk am I
without golden scales?

238
00:18:39,790 --> 00:18:41,980
I knew something was fishy about this.

239
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:43,860
There is a Barrier indeed.

240
00:18:52,430 --> 00:18:53,270
Found it.

241
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:29,140
Why am I back here again?

242
00:21:15,430 --> 00:21:16,690
Why is it here again?

243
00:22:11,390 --> 00:22:13,020
Everything here is poisonous.

244
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:14,980
This fruit

245
00:22:15,670 --> 00:22:16,740
must be poisonous too.

246
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:26,690
Anyway, I'm immune to all poisons,
so what am I afraid of?

247
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:29,450
It's better than starving to death.

248
00:23:40,480 --> 00:23:41,380
Beiyue.

249
00:23:43,030 --> 00:23:43,980
Beiyue.

250
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:45,500
Save me.

251
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:50,810
Beiyue,

252
00:23:51,790 --> 00:23:52,740
save me.

253
00:24:21,190 --> 00:24:22,030
His Highness is awake.

254
00:24:22,550 --> 00:24:23,390
Beiyue.

255
00:24:29,190 --> 00:24:30,110
Your Highness.

256
00:24:30,110 --> 00:24:30,950
Your Highness.

257
00:24:32,030 --> 00:24:32,870
Your Highness.

258
00:24:45,070 --> 00:24:46,410
Have you found Ziqing?

259
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:52,000
Your Highness, please don't move.

260
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:53,230
- Your Highness.
- Fourth Prince.

261
00:24:53,230 --> 00:24:54,070
Jun Beiyue.

262
00:24:54,270 --> 00:24:55,110
Jun Beiyue,

263
00:24:55,910 --> 00:24:58,280
no matter how much force you use
to dig that sand.

264
00:24:58,280 --> 00:24:59,160
It's all in vain.

265
00:24:59,160 --> 00:25:00,000
Do you know?

266
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:04,470
I don't believe
she would just disappear into thin air.

267
00:25:04,470 --> 00:25:05,310
I'm back.

268
00:25:05,910 --> 00:25:06,780
I'm back.

269
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:10,330
She just disappeared into thin air.

270
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,930
There is a Barrier
under Mingsha Mountain.

271
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:14,440
I read it.

272
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:16,400
In the book from the Archive Pavilion
of Nanzhao,

273
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:17,980
it is recorded

274
00:25:18,390 --> 00:25:20,040
that every Jiazi day on the Jiazi month,

275
00:25:20,040 --> 00:25:21,280
several Barriers will open.

276
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:22,660
Ziqing fell in at that time.

277
00:25:23,310 --> 00:25:24,450
Now you all understand, right?

278
00:25:25,270 --> 00:25:26,680
Chu Feiyan deliberately led Ziqing

279
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:27,820
to the entrance to the Barrier.

280
00:25:27,820 --> 00:25:28,950
When it's time, the Barrier opened

281
00:25:28,950 --> 00:25:30,260
and Ziqing fell in.

282
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:32,720
Moreover...

283
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:33,980
What?

284
00:25:35,520 --> 00:25:37,210
